{"cursor":"2688","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox album\n| Name = Melt| Type = studio Artist = Straitjacket Fits Cover = Released =\n| Recorded = , Airforce Studios, New Zealand and Platinum Studios, Australia\n| Genre = Alternative rock, Dunedin Sound Length = 43:27 Language = English\n| Label = Flying Nun Records Producer = Gavin McKillop Reviews = Last album =\n| [[Hail (album)|Hail]] (1988) This album = 'Melt' (1990) Next album =\n| [[Blow (album)|Blow]] (1993)\n}} 'Melt' was the second album from Dunedin, New Zealand band Straitjacket Fits,\nand the last to feature the original line-up of Shayne Carter, Andrew Brough,\nJohn Collie and David Wood; Brough was to leave before the third album, Blow.\nThe album reached no. 13 on the New Zealand music charts. The album would later\nsell a respectable 40,000 copies in the United States.\n\nThe album spawned three singles, \"Bad Note for a Heart\", \"Down in Splendour\",\nand \"Roller Ride\". Of these, only \"Bad Note for a Heart\" charted (reaching no.\n25 in the New Zealand charts), yet the Andrew Brough single \"Down in Splendour\"\nhas become acknowledged as the album's best song, being listed at number 32 in\n2001 on the Australasian Performing Rights Association's 75th anniversary poll\nof New Zealand's top 100 songs of all\ntime. [http://www.sharononeill.com/?page_id=29 Listing of APRA New Zealand\ntop 100 songs poll results] The music video for \"Bad Note for a Heart\"\nwon the award for best New Zealand music video of 1990. Davey, T. &\nPuschmann, H. (1996) Kiwi rock. Dunedin: Kiwi Rock Publications. ISBN 0-473-03718-\n1. p. 89\n\nThe album was seen as being truer to the band's sound than the previous album\n([[Hail (album)|Hail]]), and closer to the live sound and to the sound of the\nband's debut EP [[Life in One Chord]]. The album was described as \"...a\nculmination of searing guitars that never collide and are always textured with\nthe rhythm section's simple powerful backbone.\". [[Rip It Up (magazine)|Rip\nIt Up]], November 1990\n","linknr":109,"url":"Melt_(Straitjacket_Fits_album)","recorded":1364044340,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Melt_(Straitjacket_Fits_album)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Melt_(Straitjacket_Fits_album)&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-head","#p-search","/wiki/Studio_album","/wiki/Straitjacket_Fits","/w/index.php?title=Airforce_Studios&action=edit&redlink=1","/wiki/New_Zealand","/wiki/Platinum_Studios","/wiki/Australia","/wiki/Music_genre","/wiki/Alternative_rock","/wiki/Dunedin_Sound","/wiki/English_language","/wiki/Record_label","/wiki/Flying_Nun_Records","/wiki/Record_producer","/w/index.php?title=Gavin_McKillop&action=edit&redlink=1","/wiki/Straitjacket_Fits","/wiki/Hail_(album)","/wiki/Blow_(album)","/wiki/Dunedin","/wiki/New_Zealand","/wiki/Straitjacket_Fits","/wiki/Shayne_Carter","/wiki/Andrew_Brough","/wiki/John_Collie_(musician)","/wiki/David_Wood_(New_Zealand_musician)","/wiki/Blow_(album)","/wiki/Australasian_Performing_Rights_Association","#cite_note-1","#cite_note-2","/wiki/Hail_(album)","/wiki/Extended_play","/wiki/Life_in_One_Chord","#cite_note-3","/w/index.php?title=Melt_(Straitjacket_Fits_album)&action=edit&section=1","/w/index.php?t